summary:
The primary example illustrating antibody-dependent enhancement involves dengue fever, wherein previously formed but non-neutralizing antibodies facilitate infection by a second serotype, leading to more severe symptoms through increased cell entry and higher levels of viremia. This mechanism clearly aligns with what has been observed for this condition. \boxed{D}
To summarize Agent1’s reasoning:

Antibodies from an initial dengue virus encounter may worsen later infections when exposed to a different serotype because they fail to completely block the virus; instead, these partially effective antibodies help the virus enter cells more easily, causing greater harm—this process exemplifies antibody-dependent enhancement primarily seen in dengue fever. Therefore, the answer is D.

